abels and typed catalogue cards sit against newer interpretive text, and the tonal difference lands straight away, clipped classification next to fuller context. Display furniture gets treated as evidence too, with label rails, fixings and scuffed edges kept in view rather than tidied away. A few enlarged label texts make it easy to clock how word choice sets the tone for everything else.</p><p>Two don’t-miss elements keep the focus sharp without turning it into a lecture. The mounting section lays out real brackets, pins, foam forms and straps like a working kit, and it’s clear how “safe” and “seen” get negotiated object by object. Then the lighting studies, with filters, sample panels and simple side-by-side comparisons, show how glare, shadow and colour temperature steer attention, even when everything seems straightforward. A small grouping of case glass and backing boards makes the point quietly, reflection and contrast can change what reads as important. Notes about handling, storage and cleaning sit close by, pulling the emphasis back to everyday labour.</p><p>A hidden gem sits slightly off the main line of cases, a pocket of rejected label drafts with crossings-out, substituted words and awkward gaps where certainty disappears. Kept together rather than binned, they make the editing process feel tangible, what gets softened, what gets named, what stays vague. Around it, the practical stuff keeps pressing in, worn wooden drawers from storage, conservation-style packing materials, and plain instructions that prioritise stability over drama. In the last cluster, tiny differences in font size, line breaks and placement show how authority can sit in the smallest layout decision.</p>\n", 'max_output_tokens': 9000, 'model': 'gpt-5.2', 'reasoning': {'effort': 'medium'}, 'text': {'verbosity': 'low', 'format': {'type': 'json_schema', 'name': 'temp_translation_bundle', 'strict': True, 'schema': {'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False, 'properties': {'fr': {'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False, 'properties': {'name': {'type': 'string'}, 'short': {'type': 'string'}, 'long': {'type': 'string'}}, 'required': ['name', 'short', 'long']}, 'es': {'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False, 'properties': {'name': {'type': 'string'}, 'short': {'type': 'string'}, 'long': {'type': 'string'}}, 'required': ['name', 'short', 'long']}, 'it': {'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False, 'properties': {'name': {'type': 'string'}, 'short': {'type': 'string'}, 'long': {'type': 'string'}}, 'required': ['name', 'short', 'long']}, 'ru': {'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False, 'properties': {'name': {'type': 'string'}, 'short': {'type': 'string'}, 'long': {'type': 'string'}}, 'required': ['name', 'short', 'long']}, 'zh-CN': {'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False, 'properties': {'name': {'type': 'string'}, 'short': {'type': 'string'}, 'long': {'type': 'string'}}, 'required': ['name', 'short', 'long']}}, 'required': ['fr', 'es', 'it', 'ru', 'zh-CN']}}}}}
