2026-01-30 22:51:19,127 DEBUG openai._base_client: Request options: {'method': 'post', 'url': '/responses', 'files': None, 'idempotency_key': 'stainless-python-retry-77876f29-8d41-41df-b8b3-ec4c17d66c0f', 'json_data': {'input': "Translate the following Divento temporary exhibition content.\n\nRules (follow exactly):\n- Return ONLY a JSON object matching the provided schema.\n- Do not add citations, links, or URLs.\n- Avoid em/en dash characters (— or –); rewrite with commas or parentheses.\n- Keep all HTML tags intact in 'long' and return valid HTML.\n- Do NOT add extra blank lines/newlines.\n- For 'short': maximum 164 characters in the target language, keep natural phrasing.\n- For 'name': translate only what should be translated; keep proper nouns/titles as appropriate.\n- For zh-CN: translate ALL prose into Simplified Chinese; Latin script is allowed ONLY for proper nouns and official artwork/series titles.\n\nEnglish inputs:\n- name_en: The Coming of Age, Exhibition, Wellcome Collection, London: 26 March-29 November 2026\n- short_en: Track the awkward, tender jump into adulthood through diaries, medical objects and films at Wellcome Collection in London.\nlong_en_html:\n<p>A sequence of rooms at The Wellcome Collection grounds the show in specific works and practical context. At Wellcome Collection in London, UK, The Coming of Age keeps circling the messy handover between childhood and adulthood, not as a single moment but as a chain of tests, labels and choices. One room leans on biology and medicine, another turns to school, family and friendship, and the tone shifts between funny, uneasy and painfully familiar.</p><p>Objects do a lot of the talking. There’s a battered school exercise book packed with doodles, revision notes and a few crossed out ambitions, set near material on growth charts and health advice. Orthodontic retainers and dental moulds sit alongside diagrams that sort bodies into stages, and the effect is more blunt than nostalgic. Elsewhere, packaging for the oral contraceptive pill and straightforward pamphlets on menstruation and puberty point to how growing up gets managed through systems, not just feelings. A cluster of exam papers and report comments brings in pressure that doesn’t need any decoration.</p><p>The highlight lands where real voices cut through the official language. A run of diary pages, letters and scrawled annotations pulls attention away from neat categories and towards everyday contradictions, confidence one minute, dread the next. Don’t miss the listening station of recorded memories, awkward firsts, family rules, sudden independence, it stays with the mind because it sounds ordinary. Don’t miss the projection space either, where sex education films and public information clips loop through careful reassurance and stiff euphemisms, sometimes undercut by what people remember actually learning. The show keeps nudging between private experience and public policy without forcing a single moral.</p><p>Along the way, wall texts tie adolescence to schooling, the law, diagnosis, and the NHS, with an eye on who gets judged, who gets helped, and who gets ignored. The hidden gem is a small vitrine of acne treatments and beauty adverts, their promises of control and “clear skin” doing cultural work that’s easy to overlook. Photographs of youth groups, uniforms and bedrooms keep returning as evidence rather than decoration, and a final cluster of definitions of adulthood sits side by side, sometimes conflicting, sometimes oddly compatible.</p>\n", 'max_output_tokens': 9000, 'model': 'gpt-5.2', 'reasoning': {'effort': 'medium'}, 'text': {'verbosity': 'low', 'format': {'type': 'json_schema', 'name': 'temp_translation_bundle', 'strict': True, 'schema': {'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False, 'properties': {'fr': {'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False, 'properties': {'name': {'type': 'string'}, 'short': {'type': 'string'}, 'long': {'type': 'string'}}, 'required': ['name', 'short', 'long']}, 'es': {'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False, 'properties': {'name': {'type': 'string'}, 'short': {'type': 'string'}, 'long': {'type': 'string'}}, 'required': ['name', 'short', 'long']}, 'it': {'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False, 'properties': {'name': {'type': 'string'}, 'short': {'type': 'string'}, 'long': {'type': 'string'}}, 'required': ['name', 'short', 'long']}, 'ru': {'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False, 'properties': {'name': {'type': 'string'}, 'short': {'type': 'string'}, 'long': {'type': 'string'}}, 'required': ['name', 'short', 'long']}, 'zh-CN': {'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False, 'properties': {'name': {'type': 'string'}, 'short': {'type': 'string'}, 'long': {'type': 'string'}}, 'required': ['name', 'short', 'long']}}, 'required': ['fr', 'es', 'it', 'ru', 'zh-CN']}}}}}
