 what’s usually edited out, tiredness, shame, desire, the mess that stays.</p><p>Two don’t-miss elements sit at opposite ends of the emotional scale. One is the run of neon text works, including <i>More Passion</i>, where the cursive glow turns longing into a public sign and the spelling stays personal. The other is the film <i>Why I Never Became a Dancer</i>, which holds the room with voice, memory and a refusal to tidy up the story. The soundtrack drifts into nearby spaces and changes how the quieter works read.</p><p>Works on paper keep the hand visible, smudges included. Fast drawings and monoprints let faces appear and vanish, bodies hinted at with a few stubborn marks, and the tone stays direct rather than lyrical. Elsewhere, sewn blankets and appliqué pieces pull domestic craft into sharper territory, with stitched phrases that don’t try to behave. <i>Exorcism of the Last Painting I Ever Made</i> brings paint, walls and process into the open, turning the act of making into evidence, with traces of decisions left on show.</p><p>The hidden gem is a quieter pocket of early, tightly packed works on paper set slightly apart from the louder rooms. In that corner the language is less quotable and more private, and the marks look made in a hurry, then kept anyway. Small shifts in paper tone and pressure start to matter, and a couple of modest framed sheets hold their ground next to the bigger statements, as if the story’s still being worked out.</p>\n", 'max_output_tokens': 9000, 'model': 'gpt-5.2', 'reasoning': {'effort': 'medium'}, 'text': {'verbosity': 'low', 'format': {'type': 'json_schema', 'name': 'temp_translation_bundle', 'strict': True, 'schema': {'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False, 'properties': {'fr': {'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False, 'properties': {'name': {'type': 'string'}, 'short': {'type': 'string'}, 'long': {'type': 'string'}}, 'required': ['name', 'short', 'long']}, 'es': {'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False,