2026-01-30 22:53:28,339 DEBUG openai._base_client: Request options: {'method': 'post', 'url': '/responses', 'files': None, 'idempotency_key': 'stainless-python-retry-5477f3a1-8710-48ef-a2dd-d3fef25b759b', 'json_data': {'input': "Translate the following Divento temporary exhibition content.\n\nRules (follow exactly):\n- Return ONLY a JSON object matching the provided schema.\n- Do not add citations, links, or URLs.\n- Avoid em/en dash characters (— or –); rewrite with commas or parentheses.\n- Keep all HTML tags intact in 'long' and return valid HTML.\n- Do NOT add extra blank lines/newlines.\n- For 'short': maximum 164 characters in the target language, keep natural phrasing.\n- For 'name': translate only what should be translated; keep proper nouns/titles as appropriate.\n- For zh-CN: translate ALL prose into Simplified Chinese; Latin script is allowed ONLY for proper nouns and official artwork/series titles.\n\nEnglish inputs:\n- name_en: Wes Anderson, Exhibition, Design Museum, London: 21 November 2025-26 July 2026\n- short_en: Read how miniatures, puppets and paperwork reveal the craft behind a deadpan film world at the Design Museum, London.\nlong_en_html:\n<p>Inside the galleries at The Design Museum, the route moves from key works to supporting material and context. The tone stays practical, sticking to decisions and labour rather than screen myth. In London, the story keeps circling craft, typography, and the tiny adjustments that make a frame feel tightly controlled, with Wes Anderson’s films used as the through-line.</p><p>The highlight is a detailed model from <i>The Grand Budapest Hotel</i>, shown with production notes that pin down sightlines, paint mixes, and camera movement. Nearby, storyboards and overhead set diagrams make the famous symmetry feel engineered, not accidental. A run of prop graphics, luggage labels, hotel stationery, and deadpan signage lands with real weight, because wording and letter spacing carry as much character as a costume.</p><p>Two don’t-miss elements sit at opposite ends of the process. First, stop-motion puppets from <i>Fantastic Mr. Fox</i> and <i>Isle of Dogs</i> sit under close lighting that makes armatures, fur wear, and replacement faces easy to read. Scuffs, repairs, and finger marks matter here, showing how animation holds together shot by shot. Second, working scripts, call sheets, and annotated scene pages map timing and rhythm in plain ink, with cuts, arrows, and rewritten lines that turn jokes into beats.</p><p>Design work carries the argument. Production designer Adam Stockhausen’s drawings and set plans read like architectural documents, complete with measurements, materials, and notes on finish. Costume pieces land as design objects too, including a purple concierge jacket tied to Gustave H and Margot Tenenbaum’s fur coat and tennis dress from <i>The Royal Tenenbaums</i>. A corner of <i>Moonrise Kingdom</i> paperwork leans into invented bureaucracy, with forms, stamps, and badges that still feel oddly believable.</p><p>The hidden gem is a cluster of small paper items pinned up as if they’ve just come off a studio wall, typography tests, label mock-ups, continuity Polaroids, and scraps of ephemera. Annie Atkins’ graphic work sits comfortably among colour swatches, prop menus, and annotated contact sheets, where tiny shifts in hue and texture show up as hard choices. Display cases keep the scale intimate, so tape edges, staple holes, and worn corners stay visible alongside the neatness.</p>\n", 'max_output_tokens': 9000, 'model': 'gpt-5.2', 'reasoning': {'effort': 'medium'}, 'text': {'verbosity': 'low', 'format': {'type': 'json_schema', 'name': 'temp_translation_bundle', 'strict': True, 'schema': {'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False, 'properties': {'fr': {'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False, 'properties': {'name': {'type': 'string'}, 'short': {'type': 'string'}, 'long': {'type': 'string'}}, 'required': ['name', 'short', 'long']}, 'es': {'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False, 'properties': {'name': {'type': 'string'}, 'short': {'type': 'string'}, 'long': {'type': 'string'}}, 'required': ['name', 'short', 'long']}, 'it': {'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False, 'properties': {'name': {'type': 'string'}, 'short': {'type': 'string'}, 'long': {'type': 'string'}}, 'required': ['name', 'short', 'long']}, 'ru': {'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False, 'properties': {'name': {'type': 'string'}, 'short': {'type': 'string'}, 'long': {'type': 'string'}}, 'required': ['name', 'short', 'long']}, 'zh-CN': {'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False, 'properties': {'name': {'type': 'string'}, 'short': {'type': 'string'}, 'long': {'type': 'string'}}, 'required': ['name', 'short', 'long']}}, 'required': ['fr', 'es', 'it', 'ru', 'zh-CN']}}}}}
