2026-01-30 22:55:22,236 DEBUG openai._base_client: Request options: {'method': 'post', 'url': '/responses', 'files': None, 'idempotency_key': 'stainless-python-retry-c8077915-2e34-4f9e-89b8-f04f7f2eea6c', 'json_data': {'input': "Translate the following Divento temporary exhibition content.\n\nRules (follow exactly):\n- Return ONLY a JSON object matching the provided schema.\n- Do not add citations, links, or URLs.\n- Avoid em/en dash characters (— or –); rewrite with commas or parentheses.\n- Keep all HTML tags intact in 'long' and return valid HTML.\n- Do NOT add extra blank lines/newlines.\n- For 'short': maximum 164 characters in the target language, keep natural phrasing.\n- For 'name': translate only what should be translated; keep proper nouns/titles as appropriate.\n- For zh-CN: translate ALL prose into Simplified Chinese; Latin script is allowed ONLY for proper nouns and official artwork/series titles.\n\nEnglish inputs:\n- name_en: Painting the French Riviera, Exhibition, Royal Academy of Arts, London: 2 October 2026-31 January 2027\n- short_en: Unpick Riviera colour habits and seaside motifs, tracing quick studies, bold oils and prints at the Royal Academy of Arts in London.\nlong_en_html:\n<p>Galleries at The Royal Academy of Arts set out a clear route through materials, techniques and context. Painting the French Riviera is up and running in London, all hard light, salt air and that tricky, glittering sea. Oils, watercolours and prints sit close together, so shifts in surface and speed register straight away. The wall texts stay practical, keeping an eye on what the weather does to colour and how artists respond when everything turns too bright to trust.</p><p>The hang keeps coming back to questions painters actually wrestle with: how glare flattens a view, why shadows turn violet on a white wall, and what happens to a horizon line when the water won’t sit still. Plenty of works start as on-the-spot studies, then tighten into studio paintings, with corrections, scraped-back passages and reworked skies left visible rather than tidied away. There’s a steady rhythm between quick notations and slower, more structured compositions.</p><p>A highlight lands with the move from open coast to sheltered corners, hotel terraces, courtyards and gardens, where pattern and architecture take over from panorama. Henri Matisse’s Nice years act as a touchstone for interiors that trap southern light on tiled floors and pale walls. Pierre Bonnard at Le Cannet shifts the heat into domestic space, pushing colour until a room seems to glow from within. A thread on Pablo Picasso around Vallauris adds bite, with forms pared down until the scene reads in blocks of sun and shade.</p><p>Two don’t-miss elements come through clearly. First, a room of harbour and promenade images, masts, parasols, striped awnings and fast shadows, where brushwork stays brisk and decisions feel immediate. Second, the section on colour economy, where limited palettes still hold midday intensity, and labels call out the work of choosing a handful of pigments that don’t turn to mud under strong light.</p><p>The hidden gem sits slightly off the main flow, a quieter pocket of works on paper. Pencil scaffolding, wash tests, small compositional grids and margin notes give away the planning under a breezy shoreline view, and the paper itself carries the story, buckled edges, rubbed highlights, and thumbprints caught in dried pigment.</p><p>A few grounded studio bits sit nearby, paint boxes, palette knives and dog-eared sketchbooks, plus small maps and photographs that pin specific bays and towns to the images on the walls.</p>\n", 'max_output_tokens': 9000, 'model': 'gpt-5.2', 'reasoning': {'effort': 'medium'}, 'text': {'verbosity': 'low', 'format': {'type': 'json_schema', 'name': 'temp_translation_bundle', 'strict': True, 'schema': {'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False, 'properties': {'fr': {'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False, 'properties': {'name': {'type': 'string'}, 'short': {'type': 'string'}, 'long': {'type': 'string'}}, 'required': ['name', 'short', 'long']}, 'es': {'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False, 'properties': {'name': {'type': 'string'}, 'short': {'type': 'string'}, 'long': {'type': 'string'}}, 'required': ['name', 'short', 'long']}, 'it': {'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False, 'properties': {'name': {'type': 'string'}, 'short': {'type': 'string'}, 'long': {'type': 'string'}}, 'required': ['name', 'short', 'long']}, 'ru': {'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False, 'properties': {'name': {'type': 'string'}, 'short': {'type': 'string'}, 'long': {'type': 'string'}}, 'required': ['name', 'short', 'long']}, 'zh-CN': {'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False, 'properties': {'name': {'type': 'string'}, 'short': {'type': 'string'}, 'long': {'type': 'string'}}, 'required': ['name', 'short', 'long']}}, 'required': ['fr', 'es', 'it', 'ru', 'zh-CN']}}}}}
