2026-01-30 22:55:53,233 DEBUG openai._base_client: Request options: {'method': 'post', 'url': '/responses', 'files': None, 'idempotency_key': 'stainless-python-retry-bed4da5e-f17a-458d-a0eb-c04ff611d460', 'json_data': {'input': "Translate the following Divento temporary exhibition content.\n\nRules (follow exactly):\n- Return ONLY a JSON object matching the provided schema.\n- Do not add citations, links, or URLs.\n- Avoid em/en dash characters (— or –); rewrite with commas or parentheses.\n- Keep all HTML tags intact in 'long' and return valid HTML.\n- Do NOT add extra blank lines/newlines.\n- For 'short': maximum 164 characters in the target language, keep natural phrasing.\n- For 'name': translate only what should be translated; keep proper nouns/titles as appropriate.\n- For zh-CN: translate ALL prose into Simplified Chinese; Latin script is allowed ONLY for proper nouns and official artwork/series titles.\n\nEnglish inputs:\n- name_en: Winifred Gill, Exhibition, The Courtauld Gallery, London: 14 October 2026-10 February 2027\n- short_en: Map a London working life through drawings, letters and studio odds and ends at The Courtauld Gallery, with two don’t-miss stops and a tucked-away gem.\nlong_en_html:\n<p>Labels at The Courtauld Gallery keep attention on evidence, making the subject read through objects and craft. In London, Winifred Gill comes across as someone who works things out on paper, then carries that thinking into tools, scraps, and practical routines. The display stays close to the grain of everyday making, so smudged graphite, rubbed corners, and patched seams matter as much as finished results. It feels like a life rebuilt from what survives, not from grand claims.</p><p>The highlight is a tight group of drawings, quick pencil studies on thin sheets that still hold the speed of the hand. Lines dart, pause, and restart, and there are plenty of corrections that show decision-making in real time. Some sheets keep their working marks, with pinholes and faint guidelines still visible. Nearby, a worn paint box and a small bundle of brushes keep the focus on labour, with stained handles and dried pigment doing most of the talking.</p><p>Two don’t-miss moments sit in the quieter corners. One is a pocket diary opened to packed entries, with crossings-out, squeezed-in notes, and reminders that turn planning into a kind of sketching. The other is a run of letters, folded and refolded, where Gill’s voice stays practical, sometimes warm, sometimes brisk, especially when money, space, or deadlines press in. The paper itself carries a lot, from creases to blunt pencil underlining.</p><p>There’s also a small oil sketch on board, still visibly worked, with underpainting showing through and thumb-sized adjustments held in place rather than smoothed away. Photographs and newspaper cuttings add context without drowning the room in backstory, and a scattering of exhibition catalogues, ticket stubs, and a signed bookplate hint at networks and habits. It’s the kind of material that makes reputation feel secondary to the day-to-day grind of keeping going.</p><p>A hidden gem sits almost in plain sight: a hand-stitched sampler with initials and even thread, easy to miss until the light catches the texture. It quietly links the drawing hand to other kinds of skill, including careful mending and patient repetition, and it sits comfortably alongside paper repairs, tidy mounts, and the small acts of keeping things in use.</p>\n", 'max_output_tokens': 9000, 'model': 'gpt-5.2', 'reasoning': {'effort': 'medium'}, 'text': {'verbosity': 'low', 'format': {'type': 'json_schema', 'name': 'temp_translation_bundle', 'strict': True, 'schema': {'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False, 'properties': {'fr': {'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False, 'properties': {'name': {'type': 'string'}, 'short': {'type': 'string'}, 'long': {'type': 'string'}}, 'required': ['name', 'short', 'long']}, 'es': {'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False, 'properties': {'name': {'type': 'string'}, 'short': {'type': 'string'}, 'long': {'type': 'string'}}, 'required': ['name', 'short', 'long']}, 'it': {'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False, 'properties': {'name': {'type': 'string'}, 'short': {'type': 'string'}, 'long': {'type': 'string'}}, 'required': ['name', 'short', 'long']}, 'ru': {'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False, 'properties': {'name': {'type': 'string'}, 'short': {'type': 'string'}, 'long': {'type': 'string'}}, 'required': ['name', 'short', 'long']}, 'zh-CN': {'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False, 'properties': {'name': {'type': 'string'}, 'short': {'type': 'string'}, 'long': {'type': 'string'}}, 'required': ['name', 'short', 'long']}}, 'required': ['fr', 'es', 'it', 'ru', 'zh-CN']}}}}}
